Judge Raymond Zondo ruled that claims that he was biased against Zuma had not been made. He also denied being "friends" with the former president. Zuma's lawyers say they will file for a review. The so-called State Capture inquiry is investigating claims that Zuma and his friends, the wealthy Gupta family, illegally gained access to lucrative government contracts. All have denied the allegations of wrongdoing during Zuma's nine years as head of state; he was removed as president in 2018. --BBC--